Bought this cd today, couldn't find it on any torrent site (at least not in FLAC) so I decided to share it with you. It's a Naxos cd, which means it doesn't really cost anything at all, which means you should buy it if you like it.

It's Glenn Gould's 1954-1955 recordings of Bach's Partita No. 5 in G Major (BWV 829) and Goldberg Variations (BWV 988).

Simply incredible.
